name: 5-(a-phenylethy)semioxamazide
Reason:
The compound 5-(a-phenylethyl)semioxamazide consists of several functional groups that will influence its melting point: 
- Basic unit: Urea has a typical melting point of around 133°C due to strong hydrogen bonding capabilities. 
- Phenyl group: Typically, adding a phenyl group raises the melting point due to increased π-π interactions and Van der Waals forces, we can estimate this contribution to be around +20°C. 
- Ethyl group: Adding an alkyl chain such as an ethyl group could theoretically lower the melting point due to increased flexibility, but the effect will be minor in this case given the other more dominant groups. Its impact on the melting point can be approximately -5°C. 
- Amide groups: The presence of amide groups increases the melting point because of strong hydrogen bonding but considering they are a part of the basic urea structure, they have already been taken into account. 
- Summing up the contributions, we would expect an increase in the melting point due to the phenyl group after considering the basic urea unit.
Prediction: 148°C (133 for urea + 20 for phenyl group - 5 for ethyl group)
